## Objective
Benchmark glamour's markdown parsing and rendering pipeline with various document sizes and complexity levels. These benchmarks will guide optimization and detect regressions in the rendering path.

## Detailed Requirements

### 1. Document Parsing Benchmarks
```rust
use criterion::{black_box, criterion_group, Criterion, Throughput, BenchmarkId};
use glamour::{render, StyleConfig};

const SMALL_DOC: &str = include_str!("fixtures/small.md");   // ~100 lines
const MEDIUM_DOC: &str = include_str!("fixtures/medium.md"); // ~1000 lines
const LARGE_DOC: &str = include_str!("fixtures/large.md");   // ~10000 lines

fn bench_parsing(c: &mut Criterion) {
    let mut group = c.benchmark_group("glamour/parsing");

    for (name, doc) in [
        ("small", SMALL_DOC),
        ("medium", MEDIUM_DOC),
        ("large", LARGE_DOC),
    ] {
        group.throughput(Throughput::Bytes(doc.len() as u64));
        group.bench_with_input(
            BenchmarkId::new("parse", name),
            doc,
            |b, doc| b.iter(|| black_box(pulldown_cmark::Parser::new(doc).count())),
        );
    }

    group.finish();
}
```

### 2. Full Rendering Benchmarks
```rust
fn bench_full_render(c: &mut Criterion) {
    let mut group = c.benchmark_group("glamour/render");

    for (name, doc) in [
        ("small", SMALL_DOC),
        ("medium", MEDIUM_DOC),
        ("large", LARGE_DOC),
    ] {
        group.throughput(Throughput::Bytes(doc.len() as u64));
        group.bench_with_input(
            BenchmarkId::new("full", name),
            doc,
            |b, doc| b.iter(|| black_box(render(doc))),
        );
    }

    group.finish();
}
```

### 3. Element-Specific Benchmarks
